Package SyntSpec

Class ASCarps

java.lang.Object
SyntSpec.SSCarps
SyntSpec.ASCarps
public class ASCarps extends SSCarps
ASCarps is a class that extends SSCarps with an AS-specific genotype string and a new method for determining if a fish is "wild" or not

      public ASCarps(String newName, int newAge, double length, SSLake newLocation, SSLake bornLake, SSLake dispersal, boolean ss, String fgender, String gt, int gen)
      ASCarp constructor, with input genotype and input generation
      Parameters:
      newName - string identifier
      newAge - integer age in years
      length - length of the fish in cm
      newLocation - lake object where the fish lives
      bornLake - lake object where the fish was born
      dispersal - lake object for the fish's dispersal pattern
      ss - TRUE if the fish is sterile, else FALSE
      fgender - gender of the fish
      gt - genotype of the fish (examples: ANNFF, ASSMM )
      gen - generation of the fish. -1 if there is no countdown to death
